 User preferences for I/O providers were stored as /apps/caja-actions/io-providers/<provider_id>
 keys. They are moved to [io-provider <provider_id>] group.

 MateConf                                                 Key
 -----------------------------------------             --------------------------------------
 read-at-startup                                       readable
 writable                                              writable

 3. Sysadmin reserved mandatory keys
 -----------------------------------
 These were
   /apps/caja-actions/mandatory/
     all/locked
     na-desktop/locked
     na-mateconf/locked

 These keys are just ignored if they are not in the mandatory MateConf pool, i.e.
 if they happens to be eventually editable by the user.

 If these keys are actually in the system mandatory MateConf pool, they are renamed
 in the following way:

 MateConf                                      Group      Key
 -----------------------------------------  ------     --------------------------------------
 /apps/caja-actions/mandatory/all/locked
                                            [nact]     preferences-locked
                                            [runtime]  io-providers-locked

 /apps/caja-actions/mandatory/na-desktop/locked    <removed>
 /apps/caja-actions/mandatory/na-mateconf/locked      <removed>

P. Wieser - Jan. 2011
